annotationA: Ribosome assembly factor mrt4; Component of the ribosome assembly machinery. Nuclear paralog of the ribosomal protein P0, it binds pre-60S subunits at an early stage of assembly in the nucleolus, and is replaced by P0 in cytoplasmic pre-60S subunits and mature 80S ribosomes
annotationB: Rpb5, isoform A; DNA binding; DNA-directed RNA polymerase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter; mitotic G2 DNA damage checkpoint
